There's a piece of Harlem I can't get at.
The one them militants got their arm on.

250
00:23:31,036 --> 00:23:34,498
They could have my baby.
She's been into some of that stuff.

251
00:23:35,290 --> 00:23:38,085
Bunch calls themselves the "La Mumba's."

252
00:23:38,836 --> 00:23:40,337
Ben Buford's thing.

253
00:23:41,463 --> 00:23:43,507
I could send my people to ask them.

254
00:23:44,716 --> 00:23:45,717
Shit.

255
00:23:46,635 --> 00:23:50,973
It'd come to a shootout and when
it's all over, a bunch of dead cats.

256
00:23:52,724 --> 00:23:54,309
And maybe they'd kill Marcy.

257
00:23:57,479 --> 00:23:59,523
Yeah, you're Papa pimp to them.

258
00:24:00,899 --> 00:24:04,319
They want to see you burn
as bad as they want to see the police burn.

259
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:07,281
But kidnapping sisters,
that ain't their thing.

260
00:24:07,406 --> 00:24:10,325
The only reason anybody grabs
anybody for is money.

261
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:14,663
What other bunch in Harlem needs money
bad enough to grab my baby?

262
00:24:14,746 --> 00:24:18,709
If you believe that, what's all this
about me having a foot in whitey's trough?

263
00:24:18,792 --> 00:24:21,962
I said I think they had her.
I didn't say they had her in Harlem.

264
00:24:22,045 --> 00:24:24,756
They ain't dumb enough
to take her someplace uptown.

265
00:24:26,717 --> 00:24:27,968
It don't lay right.

266
00:24:28,093 --> 00:24:31,138
What the hell you think I need you for
if I knew who had her?

267
00:24:33,557 --> 00:24:34,850
I'm guessing.

268
00:24:36,059 --> 00:24:38,395
If they don't have her, all right.

269
00:24:38,687 --> 00:24:40,480
Maybe they know something.

270
00:24:41,565 --> 00:24:42,983
I got nothing.

271
00:24:43,817 --> 00:24:45,444
That's the job, Shaft.

272
00:24:48,030 --> 00:24:49,406
Will you take it, or no?

273
00:24:53,952 --> 00:24:55,621
I get $50 an hour.

274
00:24:56,872 --> 00:24:58,123
Plus expenses.

275
00:25:00,209 --> 00:25:02,461
And no questions asked
about how I spend it.

276
00:25:03,879 --> 00:25:05,047
You got it.

277
00:25:05,255 --> 00:25:07,799
I get a free hand to move any way I want.

278
00:25:12,304 --> 00:25:13,972
You find my baby.

279
00:25:17,142 --> 00:25:18,602
That's all I want.

280
00:25:21,772 --> 00:25:23,023
I got money.

281
00:25:25,317 --> 00:25:26,568
You spend it.

282
00:25:28,779 --> 00:25:30,197
And you find her.

283
00:25:43,544 --> 00:25:45,254
That'll get you started.

284
00:26:04,189 --> 00:26:05,983
When will I hear from you?

285
00:26:10,153 --> 00:26:12,072
When I got something to say.

286
00:26:14,616 --> 00:26:16,118
One more thing:

287
00:26:19,204 --> 00:26:23,834
You send another cat after me with a gun,
I'll kill him and I'll come looking for you!

288
00:26:25,043 --> 00:26:26,837
And I'll get you, Bumpy.

289
00:26:27,045 --> 00:26:28,338
You believe it.

290
00:26:51,195 --> 00:26:52,446
Fake mother.

291
00:27:01,246 --> 00:27:04,625
"Black man born free"

292
00:27:04,750 --> 00:27:06,543
You seen Ben Buford around?

293
00:27:06,668 --> 00:27:09,171
"The way it's supposed to be

294
00:27:09,254 --> 00:27:12,883
"Chains that bind him are hard to see

295
00:27:13,550 --> 00:27:16,887
"Unless you take this walk with me

296
00:27:17,888 --> 00:27:20,390
"The place where he lives

297
00:27:21,475 --> 00:27:25,479
"It's got plenty of names
'Slums"'

298
00:27:26,313 --> 00:27:29,316
Ben Buford used to live here.
He live here anymore?

299
00:27:30,192 --> 00:27:31,235
No, why?

300
00:27:32,027 --> 00:27:33,612
I'm looking for him.

301
00:27:33,695 --> 00:27:36,281
I am, too. He owes me six months' rent.

302
00:27:37,950 --> 00:27:39,368
Take it easy.

303
00:27:42,371 --> 00:27:45,541
"Any kind of job is hard to find

304
00:27:45,874 --> 00:27:49,044
"And that means an increase
in the welfare line

305
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:52,923
"Crime rate is rising too

306
00:27:54,132 --> 00:27:57,135
"If you are hungry, what would you do?

307
00:27:58,303 --> 00:28:01,306
"Rent is two months past due

308
00:28:02,266 --> 00:28:05,310
"And the building is falling apart

309
00:28:06,562 --> 00:28:09,731
"Little boy who needs a pair of shoes"

310
00:28:14,820 --> 00:28:18,240
Hello, ma'am. I'm looking for a guy
named Ben Buford. You know him?

311
00:28:18,323 --> 00:28:19,700
Yeah, I know him.

312
00:28:19,783 --> 00:28:22,619
- Seen him around here lately?
- Not in a long while.

313
00:28:22,703 --> 00:28:25,873
"Some of the brothers got plenty of cash

314
00:28:26,790 --> 00:28:29,960
"Chicks on the corner gonna see to that

315
00:28:30,711 --> 00:28:33,881
"Some like to smoke, some like to blow

316
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:38,010
"Some even strung out on a $50 jones

317
00:28:39,595 --> 00:28:42,431
"Some are trying to ditch reality

318
00:28:43,765 --> 00:28:46,435
"By getting so, so high

319
00:28:47,728 --> 00:28:52,900
"Only to find out
that you can never touch the sky"

320
00:28:53,025 --> 00:28:55,611
I'm looking for Ben Buford.
You seen him around?

321
00:28:55,736 --> 00:28:57,529
No, I ain't seen him.

322
00:28:58,489 --> 00:28:59,531
Thanks.

323
00:29:00,574 --> 00:29:02,868
Know what the number was today?

324
00:29:03,535 --> 00:29:06,121
"Every Sunday morning

325
00:29:06,413 --> 00:29:09,708
"I can hear the old sisters say

326
00:29:10,250 --> 00:29:14,171
"Hallelujah, hallelujah

327
00:29:14,296 --> 00:29:16,173
"Trust in the Lord

328
00:29:16,256 --> 00:29:18,258
"He'll make a way

329
00:29:19,968 --> 00:29:22,804
"I hope that he hears their prayers

330
00:29:24,097 --> 00:29:26,767
"'Cause deep in their souls they believe

331
00:29:28,769 --> 00:29:30,938
"Someday he'll put an end

332
00:29:31,688 --> 00:29:33,857
"To all this misery

333
00:29:34,775 --> 00:29:36,944
- "That's in
- Soulsville

334
00:29:43,325 --> 00:29:44,993
"Soulsville"

335
00:30:04,137 --> 00:30:06,390
- What's happening?
- Man, how's it going?

336
00:30:06,473 --> 00:30:07,558
Seen Ben?

337
00:30:08,809 --> 00:30:10,227
Ben? Ben who?

338
00:30:10,894 --> 00:30:12,729
Ben Buford. You know who I mean.

339
00:30:13,605 --> 00:30:16,358
Look, man, I don't know no Ben Buford.

340
00:30:18,110 --> 00:30:18,986
$20.

341
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:22,030
That Ben Buford.

342
00:30:22,531 --> 00:30:25,701
He's holed up on a place
on Amsterdam, 710.

343
00:30:26,827 --> 00:30:28,704
What apartment and what time?

344
00:30:29,079 --> 00:30:32,416
Third floor. There's a meeting at 9:00.

345
00:30:33,375 --> 00:30:34,960
I can't guarantee it.

346
00:30:35,752 --> 00:30:38,213
I just heard some cat tell another cat.

347
00:30:39,298 --> 00:30:41,383
They're both in the movement with Ben.

348
00:30:43,802 --> 00:30:45,762
Yeah, well, stay loose, baby.

349
00:31:16,543 --> 00:31:17,920
You all right?

350
00:31:18,921 --> 00:31:20,631
Baby, are you all right?

351
00:31:22,090 --> 00:31:25,844
I got to feeling like a machine.
That's no way to feel.

352
00:31:30,057 --> 00:31:31,600
Come here, baby.

353
00:32:45,007 --> 00:32:47,634
Had a visitor from uptown this afternoon.

354
00:32:49,136 --> 00:32:50,387
What're you having?

355
00:32:50,512 --> 00:32:52,306
A dog with mustard and onions.

356
00:32:53,307 --> 00:32:54,183
No.

357
00:32:54,266 --> 00:32:55,642
Hold the onions.

358
00:32:59,313 --> 00:33:00,314
Cold, huh?

359
00:33:05,444 --> 00:33:07,196
Well, John, what did you get?

360
00:33:14,244 --> 00:33:15,579
I got laid.

361
00:33:35,891 --> 00:33:39,478
Uptown, brother. Amsterdam Avenue.
Take your time. I'm early.

362
00:34:31,697 --> 00:34:33,073
Champ, you lost?

363
00:34:33,282 --> 00:34:34,116
No.

364
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:36,743
You live around here?

365
00:34:36,827 --> 00:34:37,786
Yeah.

366
00:34:39,246 --> 00:34:40,497
You look cold.

367
00:34:46,336 --> 00:34:47,921
Get something to eat.

368
00:34:49,089 --> 00:34:50,632
Gee, thanks, mister.

369
00:34:50,966 --> 00:34:52,301
Okay, champ.

370
00:36:11,713 --> 00:36:13,632
- Who is it?
- John Shaft, Ben.

371
00:36:32,985 --> 00:36:36,780
Unless you want more visitors,
better split up that pair out front.

372
00:36:38,991 --> 00:36:41,034
Put somebody on the basement door.

373
00:36:42,077 --> 00:36:43,412
How did you find me?

374
00:36:43,495 --> 00:36:46,039
Wasn't hard. You got a big mouth.

375
00:36:48,125 --> 00:36:50,544
- Cool it, man.
- You cool it, boy.

376
00:36:53,964 --> 00:36:56,675
Don't let your mouth
get your ass in trouble.

377
00:36:59,219 --> 00:37:01,889
- I got nothing to say to you.
- Don't jive me.

378
00:37:04,141 --> 00:37:08,145
- We've put in a lot of street time together.
- That was a long time back.

379
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:10,314
I don't know you no more.

380
00:37:10,439 --> 00:37:13,734
A lot of hard years, man.
The kind you don't forget.

381
00:37:17,738 --> 00:37:21,617
Now, I'm gonna give you one minute
to say what you came here to say.

382
00:37:22,826 --> 00:37:26,580
Then you go back out that door
you came in or I'll throw you out.

383
00:37:28,916 --> 00:37:30,459
You know Marcy Jonas?

384
00:37:30,542 --> 00:37:32,669
- Yeah, why?
- You know where she is?

385
00:37:33,170 --> 00:37:35,547
- What do you mean?
- Somebody grabbed her.

386
00:37:36,924 --> 00:37:38,926
Bumpy thinks maybe it was you.

387
00:37:41,970 --> 00:37:44,014
We don't do that kind of thing.

388
00:37:44,181 --> 00:37:46,058
You know anything about it?

389
00:37:47,768 --> 00:37:50,020
Tom, you used up your minute. Get out!

390
00:37:50,103 --> 00:37:51,605
Don't "Tom" me, man!

391
00:37:52,272 --> 00:37:54,107
- Where are the guns?
- None here.

392
00:37:54,191 --> 00:37:55,692
I'll be goddamned!

393
00:37:59,446 --> 00:38:01,198
Sonny! Sonny!

394
00:38:01,532 --> 00:38:02,574
They're coming!

395
00:38:02,699 --> 00:38:04,409
- Up on the roof?
- Yeah. Go!

396
00:38:07,830 --> 00:38:08,831
He's dead.

397
00:38:08,914 --> 00:38:10,332
Come on, come on!

398
00:38:11,542 --> 00:38:13,335
Not the roof, this way!

399
00:38:22,094 --> 00:38:23,262
Stand back.

400
00:38:24,638 --> 00:38:26,890
- What is this?
- Everything will be fine.

401
00:38:27,015 --> 00:38:29,935
- What is this?
- Go over there and be quiet.

402
00:39:20,777 --> 00:39:23,572
Everything's okay, ma'am.
No need to worry.

403
00:39:25,324 --> 00:39:26,909
Sorry about your door.

404
00:39:27,326 --> 00:39:29,077
That'll take care of it.

405
00:39:31,079 --> 00:39:32,581
You set us up, man!

406
00:39:34,833 --> 00:39:36,460
Young man, please.

407
00:39:37,628 --> 00:39:38,921
Don't do that.

408
00:39:39,171 --> 00:39:44,092
Don't ever threaten me again!
And don't call me Judas!

409
00:40:25,926 --> 00:40:29,054
Come on. It's no time
to count your dead. Come on!

410
00:40:45,154 --> 00:40:46,113
Look.

411
00:40:53,412 --> 00:40:54,538
Come on!

412
00:41:00,377 --> 00:41:01,920
This way, this way!

413
00:41:06,091 --> 00:41:07,426
One of yours?

414
00:41:08,760 --> 00:41:10,596
- No.
- Probably a finger man.

415
00:41:26,904 --> 00:41:30,574
When you lead that revolution,
whitey better be standing still...

416
00:41:31,158 --> 00:41:33,368
...'cause you don't run
worth a damn no more!

417
00:41:33,494 --> 00:41:34,870
We're done running, man.

418
00:41:34,953 --> 00:41:37,331
What the hell do you call this, man?

419
00:41:57,726 --> 00:42:00,771
I got to find out if they're after you or me.

420
00:42:11,657 --> 00:42:14,743
I'll leave you with some friends.
They're straight people.

421
00:42:15,077 --> 00:42:18,121
So don't you lay any of
that Uncle Tom jive on them.

422
00:42:24,586 --> 00:42:28,590
I don't know what's connected to what.
I can't piece them together.

423
00:42:28,674 --> 00:42:29,883
Answer that.

424
00:42:30,884 --> 00:42:35,389
It's only a half an hour since it happened.
How could I have something this soon?

425
00:42:36,431 --> 00:42:41,228
I'm not paid enough to worry about what
the Commissioner or the Mayor thinks!

426
00:42:41,562 --> 00:42:43,730
It's Shaft. You want to talk to him?

427
00:42:43,814 --> 00:42:46,441
I got a call. I might have something.
Hold on.

428
00:42:46,733 --> 00:42:48,694
No, better I call you back.

429
00:42:51,864 --> 00:42:53,490
I'm coming to see you.

430
00:42:54,199 --> 00:42:56,201
You've been holding out on me.

431
00:42:56,577 --> 00:43:00,038
I'll wait. Listen, several cats
were killed in Harlem.

432
00:43:00,122 --> 00:43:01,748
You know anything about it?

433
00:43:01,832 --> 00:43:03,625
I was there, Lieutenant.

434
00:43:13,510 --> 00:43:17,806
The Captain's at home. Call him back.
Tell him I left to chase down a lead.

435
00:43:17,973 --> 00:43:21,268
- Where are you going?
- Nowhere. Just get him off my back.

436
00:43:21,351 --> 00:43:23,979
A reporter from the News
wants an interview.

437
00:43:24,980 --> 00:43:28,442
Tell him to call the Captain.
Serves the old bastard right.

438
00:43:29,860 --> 00:43:32,362
This is that list
from the intelligence section.

439
00:43:32,654 --> 00:43:34,031
What about the pictures?

440
00:43:34,114 --> 00:43:37,409
They're getting them together now.
Said about five minutes.

441
00:43:37,493 --> 00:43:40,078
Shaft's coming down. Send him right in.

442
00:43:54,927 --> 00:43:58,222
Dina'll get you a bed made up.
Why don't you get some sleep, man?

443
00:44:00,307 --> 00:44:02,643
Got some dead brothers laying out there.

444
00:44:03,477 --> 00:44:05,395
And this ain't where I should be.

445
00:44:05,812 --> 00:44:09,316
Till we find out why they're dead,
this is the only place for you to be!

446
00:44:09,650 --> 00:44:11,235
You think like a white man!

447
00:44:11,318 --> 00:44:12,903
You don't think! You want to get wasted?

448
00:44:12,986 --> 00:44:14,530
If that's what it takes!

449
00:44:14,613 --> 00:44:16,573
Marvin's sleeping.

450
00:44:22,621 --> 00:44:25,499
I'll find out what I can and pick you up
in the morning.

451
00:44:26,583 --> 00:44:28,919
If you think I'll owe you for this,
you're wrong.

452
00:44:29,044 --> 00:44:30,629
You got nothing I want!

453
00:44:32,631 --> 00:44:34,466
You can have the girls' room.

454
00:44:39,054 --> 00:44:43,058
I got to go out. Got an extra key
so I don't wake you when I come back?

455
00:44:51,191 --> 00:44:53,610
This'll open the downstairs door, too.

456
00:44:55,279 --> 00:44:56,697
Watch your mouth.

457
00:44:56,822 --> 00:44:58,240
I'll say anything I want.

458
00:44:59,116 --> 00:45:01,743
Not in this house. Not here, you won't.

459
00:45:26,310 --> 00:45:27,311
Have a chair.

460
00:45:27,853 --> 00:45:29,438
I don't like your chair.

461
00:45:31,940 --> 00:45:33,984
You gave me nothing, Vic.

462
00:45:34,234 --> 00:45:38,447
You want to lock me up for manslaughter
'cause someone went out of my window...

463
00:45:39,531 --> 00:45:40,699
...go ahead.

464
00:45:41,116 --> 00:45:42,659
You got no deal.

465
00:45:44,661 --> 00:45:47,915
I have nothing else to give you, then.
That's straight.

466
00:45:48,749 --> 00:45:50,125
What do you got now?

467
00:45:50,209 --> 00:45:51,752
One question first.

468
00:45:51,835 --> 00:45:55,464
Anyone who could've identified those guys
with machine guns got wiped out!

469
00:45:55,547 --> 00:45:56,465
Yeah?

470
00:45:56,548 --> 00:46:00,344
Five of Ben Buford's people
and probably the guy that fingered you.

471
00:46:01,386 --> 00:46:03,931
Me? Are you sure it's me?

472
00:46:05,349 --> 00:46:08,268
I'd be sure if I knew if the guys
were black or white.

473
00:46:08,560 --> 00:46:10,521
I'd make it 80-20 they were after you.

474
00:46:10,604 --> 00:46:13,065
But Bumpy could probably tell you that
for sure.

475
00:46:13,148 --> 00:46:14,775
Just say what you got, man.

476
00:46:16,777 --> 00:46:18,445
A few things that may fit.

477
00:46:20,656 --> 00:46:24,326
Do you remember I told you that Bumpy
was doubling his crews up in Harlem?

478
00:46:24,409 --> 00:46:25,244
So?

479
00:46:25,327 --> 00:46:27,371
So, downtown we get some visitors.

480
00:46:27,996 --> 00:46:32,125
Three guys from LA, two from Phoenix,
a guy from Decatur, Illinois...

481
00:46:33,043 --> 00:46:36,505
...four guys from Philly.
Altogether about 15 that we're sure of.

482
00:46:37,339 --> 00:46:38,507
Special guys, huh?

483
00:46:38,590 --> 00:46:40,884
All suspected being guns for the Mafia.

484
00:46:41,051 --> 00:46:42,636
Just got into town.

485
00:46:42,970 --> 00:46:46,431
Most of them staying at a hotel
in the Village. Taking in the sights.

486
00:46:49,184 --> 00:46:50,185
Is that it?

487
00:46:50,269 --> 00:46:52,062
No, one thing more.

488
00:46:52,938 --> 00:46:56,275
A couple of dudes from Harlem
go across to Jersey.

489
00:46:57,025 --> 00:46:59,820
Try to kidnap some Mafia bigwig.
They blew it.

490
00:47:00,154 --> 00:47:01,822
They killed the guy's runner.

491
00:47:01,905 --> 00:47:05,033
But the man says his runner
was in Florida on a fishing trip.

492
00:47:08,287 --> 00:47:10,622
- Looks like war coming.
- It's a bad thing.

493
00:47:11,540 --> 00:47:14,585
Mafia against Bumpy.
It's hood against hood, on the inside.

494
00:47:14,710 --> 00:47:16,920
On the outside, it's black against white.

495
00:47:18,922 --> 00:47:22,885
We could have tanks and troops
on Broadway if this thing breaks open.

496
00:47:24,386 --> 00:47:26,263
Yeah, you got a point.

497
00:47:26,972 --> 00:47:29,641
This is what some of our visitors look like.

498
00:47:31,185 --> 00:47:32,853
Be a good time for it.

499
00:47:32,936 --> 00:47:34,146
What? War?

500
00:47:34,855 --> 00:47:36,565
Fishing down in Florida.

501
00:47:37,149 --> 00:47:39,776
It might help if I knew
what Bumpy hired you for.

502
00:47:39,985 --> 00:47:41,820
- Never said he did.
- He did.

503
