01:11:22,533 --> 01:11:23,575
Yeah, I did.

755
01:11:24,326 --> 01:11:25,953
But he wants to ask you.

756
01:11:26,161 --> 01:11:27,955
Now. At the station.

757
01:11:30,082 --> 01:11:31,667
Lousy timing, right?

758
01:11:32,084 --> 01:11:33,502
Gonna take me in?

759
01:11:35,462 --> 01:11:36,755
I will if I find you.

760
01:11:38,632 --> 01:11:39,675
Are you home?

761
01:11:40,175 --> 01:11:41,343
Hell, no.

762
01:11:43,262 --> 01:11:44,763
That's too bad.

763
01:11:51,728 --> 01:11:53,230
Call me when you get home.

764
01:11:54,523 --> 01:11:55,274
I will.

765
01:12:01,029 --> 01:12:03,073
"Close it yourself, Shitty."

766
01:12:28,724 --> 01:12:31,518
This is Shaft. Now get this straight!

767
01:12:32,728 --> 01:12:36,190
I'll be at Caf Reggio
on McDougall street at 12:45.

768
01:12:37,983 --> 01:12:40,235
- Got it?
- Reggio, 12:45.

769
01:12:40,319 --> 01:12:41,195
Right.

770
01:13:39,294 --> 01:13:40,295
Menu?

771
01:13:41,171 --> 01:13:42,172
Espresso.

772
01:13:43,590 --> 01:13:46,343
Don't you want a sandwich
or something with it?

773
01:13:47,302 --> 01:13:48,720
Just espresso.

774
01:14:08,240 --> 01:14:10,534
I hope you don't like lemon peel.

775
01:14:11,910 --> 01:14:13,120
Let it go.

776
01:14:14,163 --> 01:14:16,790
I think you like it. I'll go get you some.

777
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:20,127
I always forget the lemon peel.

778
01:14:52,826 --> 01:14:55,078
I'm looking for a nigger named John Shaft.

779
01:14:57,456 --> 01:14:59,333
You just found him, wop!

780
01:15:02,002 --> 01:15:03,086
Sit down.

781
01:15:03,587 --> 01:15:05,964
I have to take you to visit a lady.
Come on.

782
01:15:09,092 --> 01:15:11,011
I haven't finished my espresso.

783
01:15:12,304 --> 01:15:14,014
Why don't you have some?

784
01:15:16,517 --> 01:15:19,436
Maybe they'll put a little garlic in it,
if you're nice.

785
01:15:23,774 --> 01:15:26,443
No, thanks. But you go ahead.

786
01:15:29,905 --> 01:15:32,908
We've even got time for you
to have your soul food.

787
01:15:36,745 --> 01:15:37,913
Espresso?

788
01:15:39,206 --> 01:15:40,541
No, thanks.

789
01:15:43,919 --> 01:15:45,087
Keep it.

790
01:15:46,004 --> 01:15:47,381
Thanks, baby.

791
01:16:01,228 --> 01:16:02,312
Let's go.

792
01:17:39,576 --> 01:17:40,744
Come on.

793
01:18:13,485 --> 01:18:14,778
After you, man.

794
01:18:58,030 --> 01:18:59,281
You stay here.

795
01:18:59,364 --> 01:19:03,785
You get around the back, keep an eye
on the alley door. Stay out of sight.

796
01:19:04,119 --> 01:19:05,871
What if they come out our way?

797
01:19:05,954 --> 01:19:09,625
You follow them. Remmy,
you come back for me. Now move it!

798
01:19:23,889 --> 01:19:26,099
No noise. Now, answer me straight.

799
01:19:27,768 --> 01:19:29,311
No lies and no con.

800
01:19:30,354 --> 01:19:32,564
How many men you got in there with her?

801
01:19:32,689 --> 01:19:33,649
Two.

802
01:19:35,317 --> 01:19:36,318
Okay.

803
01:19:36,568 --> 01:19:40,989
When I tell you, you open that door like
this gun was about to blow your head off.

804
01:19:42,324 --> 01:19:44,409
No signal or you're gone. Got it?

805
01:19:45,577 --> 01:19:46,537
Yeah.

806
01:19:50,082 --> 01:19:50,707
Gin!

807
01:19:50,791 --> 01:19:51,917
Open it.

808
01:19:59,925 --> 01:20:01,718
Turn her loose or he goes.

809
01:20:03,762 --> 01:20:06,181
- Tell them to turn her loose.
- He won't.

810
01:20:07,558 --> 01:20:09,726
He won't shoot, Marcy, come here.

811
01:20:10,394 --> 01:20:12,563
There's nothing you can do, Shaft.

812
01:20:12,938 --> 01:20:16,358
Except go back to Harlem
and tell Bumpy his little girl is fine.

813
01:20:16,483 --> 01:20:19,444
- When I leave, she leaves with me.
- No way, Shaft.

814
01:20:19,653 --> 01:20:22,364
She's our ace. You never give up your ace.

815
01:20:22,823 --> 01:20:24,324
Maybe you're right.

816
01:20:24,658 --> 01:20:27,703
I should take you uptown
and turn you over to Bumpy.

817
01:20:28,704 --> 01:20:31,373
Change your mind, you can walk right now.

818
01:20:32,583 --> 01:20:35,544
You try to take the girl or me along,
you're dead.

819
01:20:35,836 --> 01:20:38,922
You trying to tell me they'd blow you away
to get me?

820
01:20:39,214 --> 01:20:40,465
That's right.

821
01:20:46,054 --> 01:20:49,892
I halfway believe you. But, you're my ace,
so I got to call you.

822
01:21:03,655 --> 01:21:06,950
The only thing that's keeping you alive
right now is...

823
01:21:07,075 --> 01:21:10,370
...you got to be fit enough
to go tell that black punk in Harlem...

824
01:21:10,454 --> 01:21:13,957
...that he's got 24 hours to deal
or he's got a dead daughter!

825
01:21:14,041 --> 01:21:15,167
And a war!

826
01:21:15,667 --> 01:21:16,877
You hear me?

827
01:21:20,088 --> 01:21:21,673
Come on, let's go!

828
01:21:22,758 --> 01:21:23,842
Let's go!

829
01:21:31,225 --> 01:21:32,476
Back door.

830
01:22:08,720 --> 01:22:09,847
Come on.

831
01:22:12,933 --> 01:22:13,976
Come on!

832
01:22:24,570 --> 01:22:26,280
You all right? Come on.

833
01:22:27,030 --> 01:22:28,073
Come on.

834
01:22:28,157 --> 01:22:29,575
You all right?

835
01:22:31,702 --> 01:22:33,328
Get me up out of here.

836
01:22:34,413 --> 01:22:37,291
The place'll be stinking with cops
in a minute.

837
01:22:39,668 --> 01:22:42,379
Grab those guns. Let's get out of here.

838
01:22:52,681 --> 01:22:55,225
- Ellie! Ellie, open up!
- Yes!

839
01:22:58,270 --> 01:22:59,980
My God! What happened?

840
01:23:00,856 --> 01:23:02,149
He's been shot.

841
01:23:05,527 --> 01:23:07,112
Put him on the couch.

842
01:23:08,238 --> 01:23:10,782
Didn't want to tell you on the phone.

843
01:23:22,753 --> 01:23:24,421
Ellie, call Sam.

844
01:23:25,047 --> 01:23:27,966
- You need a real doctor, baby.
- I said, call Sam.

845
01:23:42,481 --> 01:23:43,440
Easy.

846
01:23:52,324 --> 01:23:53,367
Blade.

847
01:23:54,660 --> 01:23:56,119
Get on the phone.

848
01:23:56,787 --> 01:24:00,123
We gonna need some more brothers.
With guns this time.

849
01:24:05,254 --> 01:24:08,006
Bumpy'll handle the transportation.

850
01:24:32,239 --> 01:24:33,907
Had to bring you to, Johnny.

851
01:24:33,991 --> 01:24:37,286
Can't fix anything else,
till you tell me where you hurt.

852
01:24:38,537 --> 01:24:40,038
Wall to wall, Sam.

853
01:24:42,374 --> 01:24:44,251
Ellie, give me that phone.

854
01:24:45,627 --> 01:24:47,504
- Get those boys?
- Got eight.

855
01:24:50,424 --> 01:24:51,717
Know where they took her?

856
01:24:51,800 --> 01:24:55,304
One of the brothers tailed them.
He's watching the place now.

857
01:24:55,637 --> 01:24:57,389
What about the back exit?

858
01:24:57,723 --> 01:25:00,142
Everything's cool, baby. Don't worry.

859
01:25:00,642 --> 01:25:02,394
Did you run into a train?

860
01:25:03,604 --> 01:25:07,107
Tight as you can get it.
I got to get up soon as you're done.

861
01:25:12,154 --> 01:25:14,573
Damn, those were some tough white boys.

862
01:25:15,199 --> 01:25:17,576
You're gonna have one hell of a time.

863
01:25:17,701 --> 01:25:20,037
Got a bad sprain on that right wrist.

864
01:25:20,204 --> 01:25:21,121
Tape it.

865
01:25:21,205 --> 01:25:24,958
I did, damn it. What do you think I am,
an amateur?

866
01:25:26,084 --> 01:25:28,962
Too good of a job, Sam.
I didn't even feel it.

867
01:25:46,438 --> 01:25:47,648
Wrong number.

868
01:25:47,731 --> 01:25:50,776
Cut the crap, man. This is Shaft.
I saw Marcy.

869
01:25:51,318 --> 01:25:52,736
Is she all right?

870
01:25:53,612 --> 01:25:55,072
Scared to death, but okay.

871
01:25:55,280 --> 01:25:58,575
I need three cabs,
on the corner of Ninth and Washington.

872
01:25:59,701 --> 01:26:02,162
- To pick up some of Ben's people.
